1
00:00:05,010 --> 00:00:06,948
Sometimes you’ll say,

2
00:00:06,948 --> 00:00:09,047
“What should be 
the first preaching point?”

3
00:00:09,047 --> 00:00:12,157
[Heartfelt Heartshare]

4
00:00:12,157 --> 00:00:14,487
Well, you could have 
a discussion about that,

5
00:00:14,487 --> 00:00:15,887
you could analyse—

6
00:00:15,887 --> 00:00:18,677
these are the kind of things 
generally people should hear first.

7
00:00:18,685 --> 00:00:22,605
ātmā‒jñāna to paramātmā-jñāna …

8
00:00:22,605 --> 00:00:25,545
there’s a sequence of how
to present these things.

9
00:00:25,555 --> 00:00:27,515
We appreciate that.

10
00:00:27,515 --> 00:00:32,125
but at the same time
I like to suggest that

11
00:00:32,125 --> 00:00:35,945
whatever it is you’ve appreciated—
share that.

12
00:00:35,955 --> 00:00:40,305
Because that would be said
in a more heartfelt way.

13
00:00:40,315 --> 00:00:48,475
It’s one thing—the rote recitation
of perceived siddhānta,

14
00:00:48,475 --> 00:00:52,222
but another thing when someone,
“What do you like about it?”

15
00:00:52,222 --> 00:00:54,262
And you say,
“Well, this is what I like.”

16
00:00:54,262 --> 00:00:56,182
Like Guru Mahārāj
always repeated about

17
00:00:56,182 --> 00:01:00,302
this one lady said, 
disciple of Prabhupād,

18
00:01:00,302 --> 00:01:02,992
when she’s visiting the Math.

19
00:01:02,992 --> 00:01:06,762
She said what she liked about
Kṛṣṇa consciousness—

20
00:01:06,762 --> 00:01:10,732
is we’re being given a chance
to have a family life with Kṛṣṇa.

21
00:01:10,732 --> 00:01:16,042
Guru Mahārāj 
quoted that for 20 years.

22
00:01:16,064 --> 00:01:19,854
You can listen in …
regularly this comes up in his talks.

23
00:01:19,854 --> 00:01:21,574
He was that impressed.

24
00:01:21,574 --> 00:01:25,334
He liked that so much
that she got it.

25
00:01:25,344 --> 00:01:30,264
Although she was 
a relatively new devotee,

26
00:01:30,264 --> 00:01:35,694
and from a foreign country,
but that appealing to her.

27
00:01:35,694 --> 00:01:40,238
When Bhakti Madhur Bon Mahārāj

28
00:01:40,238 --> 00:01:45,488
met with Guru Mahārāj,
and he was introduced,

29
00:01:45,498 --> 00:01:49,298
and he mentioned to Guru Mahārāj
he’d read the Bhagavad-gītā.

30
00:01:49,308 --> 00:01:51,988
So, Guru Mahārāj 
said to him,

31
00:01:52,928 --> 00:01:56,928
“Of what you read, 
what did you like?”

32
00:01:56,928 --> 00:02:00,598
And he said, and this scored
a lot of points for him;

33
00:02:00,598 --> 00:02:03,718
he said, “I liked the part
where Kṛṣṇa says,

34
00:02:03,718 --> 00:02:06,398
‘Give up everything 
and surrender to me’.”

35
00:02:06,398 --> 00:02:08,448
And Guru Mahārāj 
started to smile.

36
00:02:08,448 --> 00:02:12,318
[Laughing]

37
00:02:12,318 --> 00:02:14,778
So, it reminds me also of
 

38
00:02:14,778 --> 00:02:19,898
once a newspaper reporter
came to interview me.

39
00:02:19,898 --> 00:02:24,768
And it was the particular time where
the Kṛṣṇa consciousness movement

40
00:02:24,768 --> 00:02:29,118
was not getting good press,
we could say.

41
00:02:29,138 --> 00:02:37,548
And so I was really not happy
about having to do this interview also.

42
00:02:37,548 --> 00:02:43,180
Knowing that embarrassing sort 
of awkard questions were going to be asked.

43
00:02:43,180 --> 00:02:46,140
But somehow I had to do it.

44
00:02:46,140 --> 00:02:52,390
And so, we’re talking
and while we’re doing this

45
00:02:54,114 --> 00:02:56,614
Mahayogi Maharaj came into the room

46
00:02:56,614 --> 00:02:59,434
and some scholars 
were visiting from a university.

47
00:02:59,434 --> 00:03:01,064
And he wanted 
to show them 
 

48
00:03:01,064 --> 00:03:04,944
a particular tape 
of Guru Mahārāj  speaking.

49
00:03:04,944 --> 00:03:06,544
And I knew these tapes 
very well

50
00:03:06,544 --> 00:03:09,544
and where it would be, 
like which one it was.

51
00:03:09,544 --> 00:03:14,374
I said, “Oh, show them this one.”
And he went. 
 

52
00:03:14,374 --> 00:03:16,254
And he goes, “Which one is that?”
I go, “It’s the one where is said,

53
00:03:16,254 --> 00:03:19,274
‘If I had a drop of love for Kṛṣṇa
I would’ve died a long time.’”

54
00:03:19,274 --> 00:03:21,024
And he goes, “Oh, oh, yeah

55
00:03:21,024 --> 00:03:22,734
that one, yeah, right, OK. 
Right, that will be in.”

56
00:03:22,734 --> 00:03:25,584
And so, he goes out and then
I turn to this woman,

57
00:03:25,584 --> 00:03:26,704
and she is like:

58
00:03:26,704 --> 00:03:29,664
“now we have to go back 
to this stuff.”

59
00:03:29,664 --> 00:03:31,534
And she stops for a second,

60
00:03:31,534 --> 00:03:35,014
and she says, 
“Can I ask you a question?”

61
00:03:35,014 --> 00:03:37,264
And I’m saying, 
“Yes, lady. What?

62
00:03:37,264 --> 00:03:39,694
What do you want to know?”

63
00:03:39,694 --> 00:03:43,614
And she said, 
“Why did that person say,

64
00:03:43,614 --> 00:03:45,814
‘If I had a drop 
of love for Kṛṣṇa,

65
00:03:45,814 --> 00:03:49,064
I would’ve died 
a long time ago.’”

66
00:03:49,064 --> 00:03:52,944
“Why did he say that?”

67
00:03:52,944 --> 00:03:57,594
So, you wouldn’t think 
that that would be like

68
00:03:57,594 --> 00:04:00,304
what you would lead with.

69
00:04:00,304 --> 00:04:02,744
But that she found,
hearing that,

70
00:04:02,744 --> 00:04:07,834
it had some mysterious pull
on her heart and consciousness.

71
00:04:07,834 --> 00:04:10,584
She wanted to hear 
more about it.

72
00:04:10,584 --> 00:04:13,394
And that’s when I started
preaching to her.

73
00:04:13,590 --> 00:04:18,600
And I was as surprised, maybe
more surprised than her.

74
00:04:18,619 --> 00:04:21,009
Because I had a stereotype
in my mind—

75
00:04:21,009 --> 00:04:25,609
oh, this is reporter 
who’s trying to trick me.

76
00:04:25,609 --> 00:04:30,569
And I was in a very poor
state of consciousness, actually.

77
00:04:30,569 --> 00:04:36,249
But by her asking that question, 
she opened the door to another zone.

78
00:04:36,249 --> 00:04:39,029
Then I became very happy, 
we had a nice discussion ...

79
00:04:39,029 --> 00:04:41,469
everything changed at that point.

80
00:04:41,469 --> 00:04:44,809
And I would’ve never thought 
like to begin with that.

81
00:04:44,809 --> 00:04:48,749
But then we can see
Kṛṣṇa had another idea.

82
00:04:48,749 --> 00:04:52,309
So, we want to be open, 
as fallen as we are,

83
00:04:52,309 --> 00:04:56,459
as unqualified as we are.
We’ll say, “ Kṛṣṇa …”,

84
00:04:56,459 --> 00:05:00,169
like Prabhupād in his poem,
when he says,

85
00:05:00,169 --> 00:05:02,109
when he reaches America, 
I mean,

86
00:05:02,109 --> 00:05:04,399
it’s almost humorous,
but it’s not.
 

87
00:05:04,399 --> 00:05:08,389
It’s heartbreaking,
but he says,

88
00:05:08,389 --> 00:05:10,039
he’s now in America after ...

89
00:05:10,039 --> 00:05:13,599
and almost dies on the ship
on the way over—heart attack.

90
00:05:13,599 --> 00:05:14,859
And he says,

91
00:05:14,859 --> 00:05:18,489
“You must’ve brought me here 
for a reason.”

92
00:05:18,489 --> 00:05:20,509
That’s what he thought.

93
00:05:20,509 --> 00:05:25,219
How humble! How … 
I mean, it’s heartbreaking!

94
00:05:25,219 --> 00:05:28,639
Saying “You’ve brought me here
for a reason.”

95
00:05:28,639 --> 00:05:30,139
Must be!

96
00:05:30,139 --> 00:05:32,789
So, he concluded,
he said,

97
00:05:32,789 --> 00:05:37,249
“Then make me dance, 
make me dance,

98
00:05:37,249 --> 00:05:40,957
make me dance, oh Lord,
make me dance.”

99
00:05:40,957 --> 00:05:44,957
Like—use me 
to do something.

100
00:05:45,991 --> 00:05:50,431
So, that’s the proper mood 
always of the devotees.

